text: Voter turnout in Punjab in elections through the years Voter turnout in Punjab in elections through the years Punjab saw its highest-ever turnout of 78.62% in the first round of assembly elections in five states on Saturday, February 4. While the state has traditionally seen a two-way fight, the AAP's entry into the fray could be significant in determining the outcome of this election.
